SUSO leverages the power of technical SEO to help our clients grow their online revenue.

We work with challenger brands and established companies alike, maximising the performance of their keywords, driving organic traffic, and boosting online revenue.

Led by respected figures in SEO research, our Tech team is continually evolving our SEO methodologies.

Out talented search marketing experts then execute these cutting-edge strategies on behalf of our clients and conduct analysis to generate insights and identify new opportunities.

Our Mission

We execute results-driven, technical SEO strategies based on a set of core principles:

“Never Assume. Analyse & Measure.
Think Critically. Be Curious.
Stay Committed. Always Empathise. Inspire.”

Founder & CEO

Will founded SUSO in 2013 and has since grown the company from a 2 person consultancy businesses in to a 30 person digital agency. His specialism is in company growth strategies and infrastructure development. A graduate in Law from Bristol University.

Rafal Moszkowcow

Rad Paluszak

Director of SEO

rad@#

Rad is our head of strategy and leads the SEO initiatives that are applied across all our client campaigns. Originally from a programmer background, Rad’s deep technical understanding of Google’s algorithms has allowed him to become one of the world’s most talented and highly respected SEOs. His specialisms include technical SEO, software development and AI automation.

Rafid Nassir

Head of Client Relations

rafid@#

At SUSO we take our relationships with clients very seriously, and that’s why we have a dedicated manager to make sure our clients remain happy with the service. Raf works with all our clients and partners, and is the first point of communication when enquiring about our services. Previous Director of Strategy at SEO.co.uk, he’s also a very talented SEO. Specialisms include onpage and backlink analysis.

Lewis Parker

SEO Analyst

lewis@#

Lewis is an experienced content writer, turned SEO analyst. He combines the technical skills of SEO with an emphasis on creative and succinct content that focuses on satisfying reader intent and maximising topic relevance. His specialties include structuring campaigns around detailed, topic-based keyword research for maximum long term growth. Lewis graduated with honours from The University of Manchester.

deep@#

Deep is from a coding background and these skills helped him to become a very talented SEO. A methodical worker, Deep’s mathematical approach to SEO helps him achieve fantastic results for his clients. His specialisms include technical SEO and page analysis. Deep is a first-class honours graduate from Leicester University in Computer Science.

We’re hiring!

Our team is made up of technical, marketing experts from some of the UK’s top universities. Contact SUSO today if you’d like to be a part of our team journey.

See open positions

I was a Computer Science student who didn’t want to become a coder, so entering the SEO industry was a perfect fit for me because it uses the same kind of problem solving and logical thinking skills.

Since joining SUSO, I went from knowing absolutely nothing about SEO to managing and handling several successful campaigns in a matter of months.

Deep Shah Computer Science BSc, Leicester University

How Much of a Ranking Factor is Domain Relevancy in 2020?
SUSO

The SEO blogosphere is full of articles espousing the importance of building niche-relevant links, while SEO forums are overflowing with people agonising whether or not to disavow non-relevant links to remain safe from penalty.

However, the question many of these people fail to ask is: what exactly is domain relevancy and how big of a ranking factor is it?

Read More

Why Good Outreach Matters | Link Building in 2020
SUSO

Whichever way you cut it, outreach link building for SEO is hard. Even when armed with the best possible content, getting in front of the right bloggers and webmasters can be an uphill struggle – furthermore, actually securing link placements can be even harder.
